load ../invoke-result-typing.maude

--- Coverage: a field in the child's OUTPUT contract, accessed via the succeeds
--- alias, is accepted.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INVOKE-RESULT-TYPING :
  accessSucceeds(fOut) outputFields((fOut , fBoth)) failureFields((fFail , fBoth))
  =>* C:Cfg accepted .

--- Coverage: a field NOT in the output contract, via succeeds, is rejected.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INVOKE-RESULT-TYPING :
  accessSucceeds(fFail) outputFields((fOut , fBoth)) failureFields((fFail , fBoth))
  =>* C:Cfg rejected .

--- Coverage: a field in the FAILURE contract, via the fails alias, is accepted.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INVOKE-RESULT-TYPING :
  accessFails(fFail) outputFields((fOut , fBoth)) failureFields((fFail , fBoth))
  =>* C:Cfg accepted .

--- Coverage: an output-ONLY field accessed via the fails alias is rejected —
--- the fails binding is the failure contract, not the output (discrimination).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INVOKE-RESULT-TYPING :
  accessFails(fOut) outputFields((fOut , fBoth)) failureFields((fFail , fBoth))
  =>* C:Cfg rejected .

--- Bite: an output field via succeeds is NEVER rejected. The RESIDUAL soup var
--- means any rejected state is a solution, so No solution proves the correct
--- field is not wrongly rejected.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INVOKE-RESULT-TYPING :
  accessSucceeds(fOut) outputFields((fOut , fBoth)) failureFields((fFail , fBoth))
  =>* rejected RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a failure field via fails is NEVER rejected.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INVOKE-RESULT-TYPING :
  accessFails(fBoth) outputFields((fOut , fBoth)) failureFields((fFail , fBoth))
  =>* rejected RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Part (b) coverage: a field SPECIFIC to the child's declared failure class,
--- accessed via the fails alias when the class is resolvable, is accepted. Under
--- the old base-only binding this child-specific field would not have resolved;
--- binding the child's failure class is what makes it check.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INVOKE-RESULT-TYPING :
  accessFails(fChild) failureFields((fChild , fReason))
  =>* C:Cfg accepted .

--- Part (b) coverage: fallback to the base — a child-class-specific field on the
--- BASE-bound fails alias is rejected (the base has no such field).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INVOKE-RESULT-TYPING :
  accessFailsBase(fChild) baseFields((fReason , fBase))
  =>* C:Cfg rejected .

--- Part (b) coverage: the base's `reason` still resolves under the fallback — the
--- control_plane regression (`after child fails as f { fail error { reason
--- f.reason } }` with a child-local failure class) depends on this.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INVOKE-RESULT-TYPING :
  accessFailsBase(fReason) baseFields((fReason , fBase))
  =>* C:Cfg accepted .

--- Part (b) bite: the base's `reason` is NEVER rejected under the fallback.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INVOKE-RESULT-TYPING :
  accessFailsBase(fReason) baseFields((fReason , fBase))
  =>* rejected RESIDUAL:Cfg .
